title: Player of the Year: Todd Goldstein continues to haul in Nat Fyfe lead
text:
KANGAROO giant Todd Goldstein continues to bridge the gap on runaway leader Nat Fyfe in the Herald Sun Player of the Year award.
The North Melbourne ruckman has taken full advantage of an injury to Fyfe which has seen him miss the past two rounds and reduce his output.
Goldstein has polled 11 votes in the past five rounds to race to 25, now just five behind the Fremantle midfield gun.
Fyfe on 30 votes hasnâ€™t polled since he suffered the corked thigh in a controversial clash with Hawthorn star Sam Mitchell in Round 15.
Ironically, Mitchell has raced on in that time and has now moved to outright third on 22 votes.
He is one vote ahead of reigning Brownlow Medallist Matt Priddis, who dropped to fourth despite still polling one vote in the Eagles clash with the Hawks.
Other movers were Magpie Dane Swan and Bulldog Mitch Wallis who were both best on the ground in Round 19.
